/* C:\Users\Edwin Boston\OneDrive\Desktop\III\STDLIB\iii\omnia\xii_rewrite.iii
 *
 * III STDLIB - omnia::xii_rewrite
 *
 * The 40 sealed reduction rules for XII canonicalisation.
 * Per DOCS/III-XII.md S9.1 + S26.1.
 *
 * Rule families:
 *   A1-A4: Associativity (4 rules)
 *   B1-B8: IF Common-Subterm Lifting (8 rules)
 *   C1-C3: LOOP Reductions (3 rules)
 *   D1-D5: Identity / PE-Const (5 rules)
 *   E1-E2: Then null-position folds (2 rules)
 *   F1-F3: Cap-flow folds (3 rules)
 *   G1-G2: Witness/Provenance folds (2 rules)
 *   H1-H2: State-transition folds (2 rules)
 *   L1-L6: Direct pattern folds (6 rules)
 *   M1-M5: Edge-case null folds (5 rules)
 *
 * Each rule has a match_RNNN(t) -> u8 (returns 1 iff LHS matches at t)
 * and an apply_RNNN(t) -> u32 (returns the rewritten term ref).
 *
 * Termination: every rule strictly decreases MPO weight (S9.3).
 * Confluence: the 117 critical pairs converge (S9.2, S26.15).
 * Order of rule firing in xii_rewrite_apply_one: numeric R001..R040.
 *
 * Hexad: kind_compose. Ring: R0. K: 1.0.
 *
 * NIH: libc only. Sealed: xii_rewrite.mhash := SHA-256(rule bodies).
 */

module omnia_xii_rewrite

/* ------------------------------------------------------------------ */
/* Externs from xii_term                                               */
/* ------------------------------------------------------------------ */

